---
title: Pork Carnitas Tacos with Pickled Onion & Monterey Jack Cheese
description: At our local taqueria, a carnitas taco (or 5) is one of our go-to orders. After all, who can resist the rich flavor and tender texture of slow-roasted pork? Tonight, we’re creating a quick version with ground pork that uses carnitas-style seasonings: chili powder, garlic, and cumin, plus tomato paste for umami-packed richness and poblano pepper for smoky notes. It’s all stuffed into steamy tortillas with Monterey Jack cheese, pickled onion, tomato, and chipotle crema—basically, everything we crave on taco night and then some.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/pork-carnitas-tacos-08447156.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/pork-carnitas-tacos-605a44bc425f260d2d63df72-a938e443.pdf
cuisine: Mexican
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/pork-carnitas-tacos-605a44bc425f260d2d63df72
author: Michelle Doll Olson
time required: 35 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 860 kcal
  fat: 46 g
  saturated fat: 18 g
  carbohydrates: 77 g
  sugar: 14 g
  protein: 36 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1600 mg
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry all produce.

Halve and peel @yellow onion{1}; very thinly slice one half and finely chop remaining
onion. Core, deseed, and dice @poblano pepper{1} into ½-inch pieces. Roughly chop
@cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Dice @Roma tomato{1}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine sliced onion, @white wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}, @sugar{2%teaspoon}, @salt{1/2%tsp}, and 1 TBSP water. Stir until sugar and salt are mostly dissolved. Set aside, stirring occasionally, until ready to serve.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @ground pork{10%ounce} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Transfer to a #plate{} and set aside.

Heat another drizzle of olive oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add poblano and chopped onion; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Return pork to pan along with @Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, half the @tomato paste{1.5%ounce}, and 1/4 cup water. Cook, scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pan, until mixture is thickened and saucy, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

While filling cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{2%tablespoon}, a bit of onion pickling liquid to taste (start with ¼ tsp and add more if desired), and a pinch of @chipotle powder{1%teaspoon}. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between #plates{}; fill with pork filling, tomato, @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}, cilantro, pickled onion (draining first), and crema.

> TIP: Alternatively, you can put everything in individual serving bowls and let everyone assemble their own tacos.